# FeedbackFlow Project Overview

## What This App Does

FeedbackFlow is a feedback collection system with:
- **Embeddable widget** for screenshot capture, screen recording with audio, and annotation
- **Central dashboard** for processing feedback with AI-powered triage, ticket drafting
- **Export integrations** to Linear, Notion, or JSON (prd.json format for AI workflows)
- **Open source** with self-host option, or hosted version with seat-based pricing

## Tech Stack

| Layer    | Technology           | Notes                                     |
| -------- | -------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| Frontend | Next.js 15           | App Router, React 19                      |
| Backend  | Convex               | Real-time, serverless                     |
| Auth     | Clerk                | User accounts + teams                     |
| Payments | Stripe               | Seat-based pricing                        |
| Email    | Resend               | Transactional + notifications             |
| AI       | OpenAI/Anthropic     | User-provided API keys                    |
| Storage  | Convex + S3/R2/GCS   | Screenshots in Convex, videos in external |
| UI       | Tailwind + shadcn/ui | Retro design system                       |

## Key Directories

```
app/                    # Next.js App Router
├── (auth)/             # Authenticated routes (dashboard, settings, analytics)
├── (public)/           # Public routes (docs, pricing, status)
├── api/                # API routes (widget, webhooks, v1 REST API)
components/             # React components
├── dashboard/          # Dashboard-specific components
├── settings/           # Settings page components
├── ui/                 # shadcn/ui base components
├── onboarding/         # Onboarding flow components
convex/                 # Convex backend (schema, mutations, queries)
widget/                 # Embeddable widget source (vanilla TS, builds to single JS)
lib/                    # Utilities (AI, email, integrations, hooks)
e2e/                    # Playwright E2E tests
__tests__/              # Vitest unit tests
```

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev             # Start Next.js
npx convex dev          # Start Convex (separate terminal)
npm run widget:dev      # Watch widget source
npm run test            # Vitest unit tests
npm run test:e2e        # Playwright E2E
npm run typecheck       # TypeScript check
npm run lint            # ESLint
```

